{{subspeciesbox | image = Snowy Plover (Charadrius nivosus) (6326191981).jpg | image_caption = Western snowy plover | genus = Charadrius | species = nivosus | species_link = Snowy plover | subspecies = nivosus | authority = }}
The '''western snowy plover''' (''Charadrius nivosus nivosus'') is a small [[wader]] in the [[plover]] [[bird]] family. It breeds in the southern and western [[United States]] and the [[Caribbean]].
On March 5, 1993 the western snowy plover was listed as a [[threatened species]] under the [[Endangered Species Act|Endangered Species Act of 1973]]. As of June 19, 2012, the habitat along the California, Oregon, and Washington Coasts have been listed as critical.<ref name=FWS>{{Cite web |title=Western Snowy Plover Species Profile |url=http://www.fws.gov/arcata/es/birds/WSP/plover.html |website=www.fws.gov |accessdate=8 February 2016 |publisher=U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service}}</ref>
